article.headline: Norfolk St. 68, Bethune-Cookman 65
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Tony Murphy scored five consecutive points during the final 90 seconds to propel Norfolk State past Bethune-Cookman 68-65 Monday. Murphy's layup with 1:29 left, after a steal by teammate Al'Davon Thomas, brought Norfolk State (3-10, 3-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) from one-point down to a 64-63 lead. Murphy, who finished with 17 points, then hit a clutch 3-pointer with 16.2 seconds left to provide a four-point margin, 67-63. The Wildcats used a quick lay-in by Demetrius Coleman to slice the difference to two. Then Norfolk State's Calvin Brown canned a free throw with 9.6 seconds left to make it 68-65. Bethune-Cookman worked for a final 3-point attempt by Jimmy Hudson at the buzzer, but it bounded high off the back of the rim. Tynell Dunkley paced the winning Spartans with 19 points, with Brown supplying 18. Bethune-Cookman (2-11, 0-4), which lost for the tenth straight time, was led by Hudson, who hit six 3-pointers and finished with 23 points. Demetrius Coleman added 11.
